responses: {"Q0":"I tried to pronounce in french to remember but then, the same sound \"an\" and \"en\" or \"in\" and \"im\" were the same sound and it was a bit confusing, so I tried to pronounce all the letters when reading and pronounce it like in german, in English or in latin and also emphasize on accent or double letters. When it was a word with two r for example arriba, I would say : aRRRRRRRRRiba as I would know three times the same letter is quite rare. Same for accent like : abôlu, I would say abOOOOOOOOOOOOlu."}
